    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>I Was Right</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Verne Hendrick letter agrees with Stephen Sondheim and Ned Rorem's declarations, in April 30 article on difference between opera and musicals, that they are not interested in human voice, per se</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>At last, confirmation of what my minority of one's ears have told me all along. Rorem: ''Actually, I was never that interested in the human voice, per se.'' Sondheim: ''Neither am I.'' Out of the mouths of horses!</p>
        <p>VERNE HENDRICK  Columbus, Ohio</p>
      </block>
